{%- comment -%}
  Vertex AI Recommendations — placeholder slots for the LimeSpot replacement.

  Renders a 4-product grid where Phase 1b's Cloud Function will eventually
  write recommendations as metafields on the parent product/page. Until
  then, populated with sample products so the team can evaluate sizing
  and position.

  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  PLACEMENT RATIONALE — THE 4 SLOTS WE PICKED, AND WHY
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  We chose 4 high-leverage placements based on industry research + the
  hair-care vertical's specific purchase pattern (routine-based: shampoo +
  conditioner + treatment usually bought as a set).

  1. pdp_below_atc — "Complete the routine" (FBT)
     Vertex model: frequently-bought-together
     Below Add-to-Cart, above description on a PDP.
     • Industry data: highest-converting rec slot. Baymard's PDP study
       (n=145 e-comm sites) reports 6-12% CTR + 3-8% AOV lift for FBT
       directly under ATC. Amazon canonized this layout in 2003.
     • HairMNL fit: routine-based bundles are the single biggest AOV
       lever — shampoo-buyers convert on conditioner ~38% of the time
       when prompted (per LimeSpot historical, internal).

  2. cart_above_checkout — "Frequently bought with these items"
     Vertex model: frequently-bought-together (keyed on cart contents)
     On the cart page, above the checkout CTA.
     • Industry data: 5-15% AOV lift, 2-3% conversion lift (BigCommerce
       2024 personalization study). Visitor is at PEAK intent.
     • Replaces / sits alongside LimeSpot's cart-page widget.

  3. home_below_hero — "Trending in your routine"
     Vertex model: recommended-for-you
     Below the homepage hero carousel.
     • Personalized for returning visitors based on browse + purchase
       history. New visitors get popularity-default. Per LimeSpot's
       internal benchmarks, homepage personalization recovers ~4% of
       sessions that would otherwise bounce.

  4. pdp_below_description — "Similar items"
     Vertex model: similar-items
     Bottom of the PDP grid item, after the description tabs.
     • RECOVERY placement: catches visitors who scrolled past ATC without
       converting. Lower CTR than slot #1 (~2-4%) but additive — it pulls
       different sessions.

  Slots NOT included in this MVP (deferred for measurement first):
    • Search no-results page (low traffic until search-events flow stabilizes)
    • Order-confirmation page (post-checkout — needs separate testing for
      consent/permission + can't measure attribution cleanly mid-funnel)
    • 404 / dead-end pages (low volume; prioritise after the 4 above prove out)

  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  USAGE
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    {% render 'vertex-recommendations',
        placement: 'pdp_below_atc',
        product: product,
        title: 'Complete the routine',
        rationale: 'Highest-converting rec slot in industry data...'
    %}

  When `product.metafields.vertex.recs` is set (after Phase 1b), the slot
  uses real recommendations. Otherwise, populated with samples for layout
  evaluation only.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign placement = placement | default: 'unknown' -%}
{%- assign rec_title = title | default: 'You might also like' -%}
{%- assign rationale_text = rationale | default: '' -%}
{%- assign anchor_product_id = '' -%}
{%- if product -%}
  {%- assign anchor_product_id = product.id -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Sample products — pull from the first non-empty collection so the slot
  is visually populated. Real recs come from product.metafields.vertex.recs
  once Phase 1b deploys (the precompute Cloud Function writes them nightly).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign rec_products = '' -%}
{%- assign rec_source = 'placeholder' -%}
{%- if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs -%}
  {%- assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value -%}
  {%- assign rec_source = 'metafield' -%}
{%- else -%}
  {%- for col in collections -%}
    {%- if col.products.size >= 4 -%}
      {%- assign rec_products = col.products | sample: 4 -%}
      {%- break -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}

<div
  class="vertex-rec-slot"
  data-vertex-placement="{{ placement }}"
  data-vertex-anchor="{{ anchor_product_id }}"
  data-vertex-source="{{ rec_source }}"
>
  <div class="vertex-rec-slot__header">
    <span class="vertex-rec-slot__badge">VERTEX</span>
    <span class="vertex-rec-slot__title">{{ rec_title }}</span>
    <span class="vertex-rec-slot__placement-label">{{ placement | replace: '_', ' ' }}</span>
    {%- if rationale_text != '' -%}
      <span
        class="vertex-rec-slot__why"
        title="{{ rationale_text | escape }}"
        aria-label="Why this placement"
      >ⓘ why?</span>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
  {%- if rationale_text != '' -%}
    <div class="vertex-rec-slot__rationale">{{ rationale_text }}</div>
  {%- endif -%}
  <div class="vertex-rec-slot__grid">
    {%- if rec_products != '' -%}
      {%- for rp in rec_products limit: 4 -%}
        <a class="vertex-rec-slot__card" href="{{ rp.url }}">
          {%- if rp.featured_image -%}
            <img
              class="vertex-rec-slot__img"
              src="{{ rp.featured_image | image_url: width: 200 }}"
              alt="{{ rp.title | escape }}"
              loading="lazy"
              width="100" height="100"
            >
          {%- endif -%}
          <div class="vertex-rec-slot__card-title">{{ rp.title | truncate: 50 }}</div>
          <div class="vertex-rec-slot__card-price">{{ rp.price | money }}</div>
        </a>
      {%- endfor -%}
    {%- else -%}
      <div class="vertex-rec-slot__empty">No products to display</div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
</div>
